==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thermocurrent
<hw>Ther"mo*cur`rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thermo-</ets> + <ets>current</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A current developed or set in motion by heat;
specif., an electric current, in a heterogeneous circuit, due to
differences of temperature between the junctions of the substances of
which the circuit is composed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermodin</ent>⟦br⟧
